WEBVTT

00:02.173 --> 00:04.375
COME ON, BOY.
 COME THROUGH THE TUBE.

00:04.375 --> 00:06.237
COME ON, BOY.
 I´VE GOT A TREAT.

00:06.237 --> 00:07.408
WHAT´S GOING ON, MAX?

00:07.408 --> 00:08.679
I´M TRAINING MR. NEEDLES.

00:08.679 --> 00:11.112
I WANT TO ENTER HIM IN
 THE DOG SHOW.

00:11.112 --> 00:12.543
DOES MR. NEEDLES
 HAVE PAPERS?

00:12.543 --> 00:14.685
OH, NO, ´CAUSE I DON´T
 THINK IT´S RIGHT

00:14.685 --> 00:18.189
THAT MR. NEEDLES HAS PAPERS
 AND SOME OF OUR RELATIVES DON´T.

00:21.052 --> 00:22.753
HEY, MAX...

00:22.753 --> 00:26.257
MAYBE MR. NEEDLES NEEDS TO SEE
 YOU RUN THE COURSE,

00:26.257 --> 00:28.729
YOU KNOW, SO HE KNOWS
 WHAT TO DO.

00:28.729 --> 00:30.030
OKAY.

00:31.462 --> 00:33.204
PAY ATTENTION,
 MR. NEEDLES.

00:33.204 --> 00:35.306
I´M ONLY GONNA SHOW
 YOU THIS ONCE.

00:47.178 --> 00:49.480
[ GRUNTING ]

00:56.227 --> 00:57.428
EW.

00:57.428 --> 01:00.761
I KNOW WHERE THAT
 TONGUE´S BEEN.

01:00.761 --> 01:04.334
I´M REALLY SORRY
 TO HEAR THAT.

01:04.334 --> 01:07.298
OF COURSE
 WE CAN COME DOWN.

01:07.298 --> 01:10.201
OKAY, TAKE CARE.
 BYE.

01:12.303 --> 01:14.375
I´VE GOT SOME BAD NEWS.

01:14.375 --> 01:17.108
OH, THAT´S GOOD --
 LOTS OF DRAMA.

01:17.108 --> 01:19.750
LISTEN, WHEN YOU SAY IT,
 GO LIKE THIS,

01:19.750 --> 01:22.183
AND THEN GO
 ♫ DUN DUN DUN! ♫

01:24.285 --> 01:25.316
NO.

01:25.316 --> 01:27.188
THIS IS SERIOUS.

01:27.188 --> 01:30.591
NOW, THAT WAS UNCLE JOE´S
 GIRLFRIEND.

01:30.591 --> 01:32.793
YOUR BROTHER´S DYING,
 BENNY.

01:32.793 --> 01:35.266
OH, MAN.

01:35.266 --> 01:36.297
SO?

01:36.297 --> 01:38.199
WHAT´S THE BAD NEWS?

01:39.430 --> 01:41.502
COME ON, MOM!
 DON´T BE LIKE THAT!

01:41.502 --> 01:43.204
BENNY, I KNOW HOW YOU
 FEEL ABOUT JOE,

01:43.204 --> 01:46.407
BUT HE WANTS YOU TO GO DOWN
 TO SAN DIEGO TO SAY GOODBYE.

01:46.407 --> 01:48.139
I SAID GOODBYE TO HIM
 15 YEARS AGO

01:48.139 --> 01:50.211
WHEN HE CHEATED ME
 OUT OF MY MONEY.

01:53.544 --> 01:55.216
I DON´T BELIEVE HER!

01:55.216 --> 01:58.289
THE MAN IS DYING AND SHE´S
 NOT GONNA TALK TO HIM

01:58.289 --> 02:01.722
BECAUSE OF SOME STUPID GRUDGE
 OVER A SUPER BOWL BET?

02:01.722 --> 02:03.424
THE LOPEZES
 ARE PROUD PEOPLE,

02:03.424 --> 02:06.527
AND WHEN THERE´S PRINCIPLE AT
 STAKE, WE DON´T COMPROMISE.

02:06.527 --> 02:08.299
THAT´S JUST
 THE LOPEZ WAY.

02:08.299 --> 02:11.362
THEY´RE FIGHTING OVER $20.

02:11.362 --> 02:15.306
WE´RE PETTY, TOO.

02:15.306 --> 02:16.467
THIS IS SO SAD.

02:16.467 --> 02:18.469
JOE´S NOT EVEN THAT OLD.

02:18.469 --> 02:20.671
HIS GIRLFRIEND DIDN´T
 SAY WHAT HE HAD,

02:20.671 --> 02:22.213
AND I DIDN´T WANT TO ASK.

02:22.213 --> 02:24.915
I BET IT WAS THE BUMP.

02:24.915 --> 02:26.717
THE BUMP?

02:26.717 --> 02:29.320
YEAH, REMEMBER WHEN I TOLD YOU
 HE VISITED TWO YEARS AGO,

02:29.320 --> 02:32.253
HE HAD A HUGE BUMP ON THE SIDE
 OF HIS NECK?

02:32.253 --> 02:34.425
[ WHISTLING ]

02:34.425 --> 02:35.856
GEORGIE!

02:35.856 --> 02:37.828
UNCLE JOE!

02:37.828 --> 02:39.159
WHOA!

02:39.159 --> 02:41.332
GIMME A HUG.

02:41.332 --> 02:42.363
HEY --

02:42.363 --> 02:44.695
HEY!

02:44.695 --> 02:46.937
WOW,
 IT´S BEEN A LONG TIME.

02:46.937 --> 02:50.471
ANYTHING, UH, NEW GOING ON
 IN YOUR LIFE, JOE?

02:50.471 --> 02:52.703
SAME OLD,
 SAME OLD.

02:52.703 --> 02:54.475
SO NOTHING´S NEW.

02:54.475 --> 02:57.208
I GUESS NOTHING´S
 POPPED UP?

02:57.208 --> 02:59.780
NO, BUT I COULD USE A SODA,
 THOUGH.

02:59.780 --> 03:02.453
LONG TRIP FROM SAN DIEGO,
 YOU KNOW?

03:02.453 --> 03:07.318
HOW WAS THE TRAFFIC, JOE?
 WAS IT BUMP-- UH...

03:07.318 --> 03:09.420
BUMPER TO BUMPER?

03:09.420 --> 03:13.224
A LITTLE BIT, BUT I HAD TO COME
 UP AND TALK TO YOUR MAMA.

03:13.224 --> 03:15.195
I WANT
 TO MAKE THINGS RIGHT.

03:15.195 --> 03:16.567
OH, HEY, MAN.

03:16.567 --> 03:19.630
WOW, HEARING THAT GIVES ME
 A LUMP IN MY THROAT.

03:22.233 --> 03:24.375
OR A LITTLE TO THE LEFT.

03:26.307 --> 03:29.240
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT COMING
 OUT OF YOUR NECK?!

03:29.240 --> 03:31.682
IT LOOKS LIKE YOU´RE
 GROWING A SECOND HEAD!

03:31.682 --> 03:34.415
WHO TOLD YOU?

03:34.415 --> 03:35.986
THE HEAD TOLD ME!

03:35.986 --> 03:39.250
IT WENT LIKE THIS --
 ORALE.

03:39.250 --> 03:41.652
IF YOU DON´T LIKE IT,
 DON´T LOOK AT IT.

03:41.652 --> 03:45.256
JOE, THAT LOOKS SERIOUS.
 HAVE YOU BEEN TO THE DOCTOR?

03:45.256 --> 03:48.459
I´M TREATING IT MYSELF.
 I DRINK WARM GINGER ALE.

03:48.459 --> 03:50.731
WELL, IF IT GETS ANY
 BIGGER, JOE,

03:50.731 --> 03:53.704
YOU CAN USE THE CAR-POOL LANE
 GOING HOME.

03:56.236 --> 03:59.310
JOE?!

03:59.310 --> 04:02.373
BENNY, I´M READY TO SETTLE
 OUR BET.

04:02.373 --> 04:04.445
I BROUGHT YOU YOUR MONEY.

04:04.445 --> 04:07.378
WHERE ARE YOU KEEPING IT,
 IN YOUR NECK WALLET?!

04:07.378 --> 04:09.019
WHAT THE HELL IS
 THAT THING?!

04:09.019 --> 04:10.751
IT´S FINE.
 DON´T WORRY ABOUT IT.

04:10.751 --> 04:12.683
LOOK,
 I DIDN´T COME HERE TO FIGHT.

04:12.683 --> 04:15.025
I CAME TO MAKE PEACE
 WITH MY ONLY SISTER.

04:15.025 --> 04:16.887
I GOT YOUR MONEY.

04:18.789 --> 04:20.491
THAT´S $10.
 YOU OWE ME $20.

04:20.491 --> 04:22.663
I STILL DON´T THINK I OWE YOU
 ANYTHING,

04:22.663 --> 04:25.796
BUT I´M WILLING TO MEET YOU
 HALFWAY, SO TAKE THE $10.

04:25.796 --> 04:27.668
NO, IT´S $20 OR NOTHING.

04:27.668 --> 04:30.571
WHY CAN´T YOU JUST CALL IT EVEN
 SO WE CAN BURY THE HATCHET?

04:30.571 --> 04:33.874
SPEAKING OF HATCHET,
 JOE, YOU MIGHT WANT TO...

04:36.407 --> 04:39.410
YOU KNOW, I DON´T GIVE A CRAP
 ABOUT THE $20, OKAY?

04:39.410 --> 04:40.711
YOU CHEATED ME.

04:40.711 --> 04:42.783
OF COURSE, I SHOULD
 HAVE KNOWN BETTER

04:42.783 --> 04:44.785
TO LET MY BROTHER
 BE MY BOOKIE.

04:44.785 --> 04:45.816
I DID NOT CHEAT YOU.

04:45.816 --> 04:47.518
YES, YOU DID.

04:47.518 --> 04:48.689
NO, I DIDN´T!

04:48.689 --> 04:50.060
OH!

04:50.060 --> 04:52.993
LOOK, MOM, WHAT FELL OUT
 OF JOE´S POCKET.

04:52.993 --> 04:54.495
IT´S A 20!
 SEE? THERE.

04:54.495 --> 04:56.527
PROBLEM SOLVED.
 NOW KISS AND MAKE UP.

04:56.527 --> 04:59.870
I´M NOT TAKING IT UNLESS HE
 GIVES IT TO ME.

04:59.870 --> 05:01.732
I´M NOT GIVING IT TO YOU.

05:01.732 --> 05:03.734
UH...
 [ CHUCKLES ]

05:03.734 --> 05:05.676
JOE, THAT´S MY 20.

05:05.676 --> 05:06.807
NO, IT ISN´T.

05:06.807 --> 05:08.579
COME ON, MAN, IT IS!

05:08.579 --> 05:09.780
NO, IT ISN´T.

05:09.780 --> 05:11.812
SEE?!
 YOU SEE HOW HE IS, GEORGE?!

05:11.812 --> 05:13.814
AH, FORGET IT.
 YOU´RE NEVER GONNA CHANGE.

05:13.814 --> 05:16.817
YOU´RE THE SAME NASTY, BITTER
 WOMAN YOU´VE ALWAYS BEEN,

05:16.817 --> 05:18.889
EXCEPT NOW
 YOU´RE AN INCH SHORTER!

05:18.889 --> 05:23.323
WELL, SCREW YOU AND THE BUMP
 THAT RODE IN ON YOU!

05:25.756 --> 05:27.958
WONDER HOW BIG THE BUMP
 IS NOW.

05:27.958 --> 05:32.503
WELL...GINGER ALE IS GOOD FOR
 TREATING GROWTHS...

05:32.503 --> 05:36.437
AS LONG AS YOU TAKE IT
 WITH CHEMOTHERAPY!

05:36.437 --> 05:39.440
LOOK, YOU HAVE GOTTA CONVINCE
 YOUR MOTHER TO VISIT JOE.

05:39.440 --> 05:40.811
SHE NEEDS CLOSURE.

05:40.811 --> 05:43.113
IF HE DIES BEFORE SHE GETS A
 CHANCE TO TALK TO HIM,

05:43.113 --> 05:45.816
SHE´S GONNA REGRET IT
 FOR THE REST OF HER LIFE.

05:45.816 --> 05:48.649
ANGIE, MY MOM DOESN´T REGRET
 ANYTHING.

05:48.649 --> 05:52.583
EXCEPT MAYBE NOT GETTING A
 BIGGER TV DURING THE RIOTS.

05:56.457 --> 05:58.358
ALL RIGHT.
 I´LL TALK TO HER.

06:01.492 --> 06:03.894
MOM, ANGIE WANTS ME
 TO TALK TO YOU.

06:03.894 --> 06:06.437
SAVE YOUR BREATH.
 I´M NOT SEEING JOE.

06:06.437 --> 06:07.868
BUT HE´S DYING.

06:07.868 --> 06:11.402
I MEAN, THIS IS YOUR LAST CHANCE
 TO MAKE THINGS RIGHT,

06:11.402 --> 06:12.403
TO GET CLOSURE.

06:12.403 --> 06:14.044
CLOSURE?!
 YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:14.044 --> 06:17.548
I WOULD RATHER GIVE BIRTH TO YOU
 AS A GROWN MAN

06:17.548 --> 06:18.909
THAN SEE THAT SNAKE.

06:18.909 --> 06:21.412
HOW CAN YOU TREAT YOUR ONLY
 BROTHER THIS WAY?

06:21.412 --> 06:22.753
HOW?

06:22.753 --> 06:25.015
I´LL TELL YOU HOW --
 YOU DON´T SCREW FAMILY.

06:25.015 --> 06:27.888
JOE AND I GREW UP TOGETHER.
 WE SHARED A ROOM.

06:27.888 --> 06:29.820
OH, BUT NOW
 THAT HE´S GOT MONEY,

06:29.820 --> 06:31.522
NOW THAT HE WEARS
 GOLD CHAINS

06:31.522 --> 06:33.694
AND GOES TO THE SUPER BOWL
 EVERY YEAR,

06:33.694 --> 06:36.897
HE CAN´T GIVE UP 20 FREAKIN´
 BUCKS TO HIS OWN SISTER!

06:36.897 --> 06:39.099
LOOK, YOUR MOM´S GONE
 AND YOUR DAD´S GONE.

06:39.099 --> 06:41.502
HE´S ALL YOU HAVE LEFT!
 FORGET THE 20!

06:41.502 --> 06:44.174
YOU SAID IT YOURSELF --
 YOU DON´T SCREW FAMILY!

06:46.507 --> 06:48.639
I DON´T KNOW.

06:48.639 --> 06:51.582
WE´RE A PROUD PEOPLE.

06:51.582 --> 06:54.485
SAVE IT FOR SOMEBODY THAT
 DOESN´T KNOW US.

06:54.485 --> 06:58.689
YOU HAVE A BIRTHDAY DINNER
 EVERY MONTH AT DENNY´S.

06:58.689 --> 07:00.521
WE´RE NOT THAT PROUD.

07:00.521 --> 07:02.523
WELL...

07:02.523 --> 07:05.496
COME ON, MOM!

07:05.496 --> 07:07.197
YOU KNOW...

07:07.197 --> 07:11.532
HE MIGHT NOT BE USING HIS
 SUPER BOWL TICKETS THIS YEAR.

07:11.532 --> 07:15.466
HE COULD GIVE THEM TO
 A FORGIVING SISTER.

07:17.938 --> 07:19.810
YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:19.810 --> 07:21.542
I NEED CLOSURE.

07:23.574 --> 07:26.076
[ INTRO TO WAR´S "LOW RIDER"
 PLAYS ]

07:36.887 --> 07:40.961
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS
 KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

07:43.093 --> 07:47.898
♫ THE LOW RIDER
 IS A LITTLE HIGHER ♫

08:14.925 --> 08:17.027
IS MY MOM STILL IN
 WITH JOE?

08:17.027 --> 08:19.800
YEAH!
 WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?!

08:19.800 --> 08:21.932
I TOLD YOU I WAS GONNA GET
 SANDWICHES.

08:21.932 --> 08:23.203
THAT WAS HOURS AGO!

08:23.203 --> 08:26.006
I HAVE BEEN HIT ON BY FOUR OF
 YOUR COUSINS,

08:26.006 --> 08:29.039
AND ONE OF THEM
 WAS SO OVERCOME WITH GRIEF,

08:29.039 --> 08:31.812
HE COLLAPSED INTO MY LAP
 AND STAYED THERE.

08:31.812 --> 08:35.184
HEY, JIMMY´S HERE!
 I TAUGHT HIM THAT MOVE.

08:35.184 --> 08:38.018
WHERE´S JOE?

08:38.018 --> 08:39.850
WE´RE HIS COUSINS FROM
 ALBUQUERQUE.

08:39.850 --> 08:42.222
OH, I´M ANGIE, AND THIS IS
 HIS NEPHEW GEORGE.

08:42.222 --> 08:44.595
JOE´S IN HIS BEDROOM
 WITH HIS SISTER.

08:44.595 --> 08:47.698
OH, CRAP!
 SHE´S GONNA TAKE THE TICKETS!

08:47.698 --> 08:49.099
WHAT TICKETS?

08:49.099 --> 08:50.961
JOE´S SUPER BOWL TICKETS.

08:50.961 --> 08:54.004
WHY DO YOU THINK WE DROVE ALL
 THE WAY HERE FROM ALBUQUERQUE?

08:54.004 --> 08:57.768
GEORGE, DID YOUR MOM COME DOWN
 HERE FOR SUPER BOWL TICKETS?

08:57.768 --> 08:59.039
TICKETS?

08:59.039 --> 09:01.041
I DON´T KNOW ANYTHING
 ABOUT TICKETS.

09:01.041 --> 09:03.043
GENTLEMEN, WHAT IS THIS
 PERTAINING TO?

09:08.118 --> 09:10.921
YOU OKAY?

09:10.921 --> 09:12.923
THAT WAS TOUGH.

09:12.923 --> 09:15.155
HE´S REALLY DYING.

09:15.155 --> 09:16.787
I KNOW.

09:19.259 --> 09:20.991
[ SIGHS ]

09:20.991 --> 09:24.094
WE SAT THERE AND TALKED
 LIKE WE WERE KIDS AGAIN,

09:24.094 --> 09:26.997
AND THEN I REALIZED
 WHEN JOEY GOES,

09:26.997 --> 09:31.201
THERE´LL BE NO ONE LEFT TO
 REMEMBER MY CHILDHOOD BUT ME.

09:32.603 --> 09:34.344
SO YOU GOT CLOSURE?

09:34.344 --> 09:37.307
YEAH.
 OH, AND I GOT THE TICKETS.

09:37.307 --> 09:38.879
YOU KNOW WHAT?

09:38.879 --> 09:42.653
I DON´T EVEN REALLY CARE
 ABOUT ´EM NOW.

09:42.653 --> 09:45.215
MOM, YOU DON´T HAVE TO
 DO THIS.

09:45.215 --> 09:48.218
YOU DESERVE ´EM.
 YOU GOT ME DOWN HERE.

09:48.218 --> 09:51.922
BENNY, I KNOW THIS WASN´T
 EASY FOR YOU.

09:51.922 --> 09:54.625
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU?!

09:54.625 --> 09:58.699
ANYTHING TO GET A HUG!

09:58.699 --> 10:02.673
I FEEL SORRY
 FOR YOUR KIDS.

10:02.673 --> 10:05.135
GEORGE, DON´T YOU THINK
 WE SHOULD GO IN

10:05.135 --> 10:06.907
AND SAY GOODBYE
 TO JOE NOW?

10:06.907 --> 10:09.740
I DON´T WANT TO SEE HIM
 LIKE THIS, ANGIE.

10:09.740 --> 10:10.881
I´LL CALL HIM.

10:10.881 --> 10:12.312
GEORGE,
 YOU SHOULD SEE HIM.

10:12.312 --> 10:13.744
I DON´T KNOW, ANGIE.

10:13.744 --> 10:16.016
WHAT IF I´M IN THERE,
 AND IT´S DARK,

10:16.016 --> 10:18.989
AND DEATH COMES IN
 AND TAKES THE WRONG MEXICAN?

10:23.253 --> 10:25.025
HEY, GEORGE.

10:25.025 --> 10:29.059
I HEARD YOU WENT DOWN TO SEE
 YOUR UNCLE AND HE´S REAL SICK.

10:29.059 --> 10:32.763
SO I THOUGHT I´D KEEP YOU
 COMPANY TODAY...

10:32.763 --> 10:35.906
OR TOMORROW...
 OR SUPER BOWL SUNDAY.

10:37.337 --> 10:39.069
YOU HEARD I HAVE AN
 EXTRA TICKET.

10:39.069 --> 10:40.741
YOU DO?!

10:40.741 --> 10:44.044
HEY, DON´T GIVE IT TO HIM, FOOL.
 I´M YOUR ASSISTANT.

10:44.044 --> 10:47.117
I DO ALL THE CRAP YOU
 DON´T WANT TO DO.

10:47.117 --> 10:48.679
GIVE ME THE TICKET.

10:48.679 --> 10:50.681
LET´S SEE WHERE YOU ARE
 ON THE LIST.

10:50.681 --> 10:54.324
OKAY, THERE´S ANGIE, ERNIE,
 EVERYONE ELSE ON THE PLANET,

10:54.324 --> 10:56.727
ALL THE DOGS AND CATS,
 AND THEN YOU.

10:56.727 --> 10:58.929
SO, YEAH,
 IT COULD HAPPEN.

11:00.731 --> 11:03.694
DUDE, YOU´RE GOING
 TO THE SUPER BOWL.

11:03.694 --> 11:05.736
THANK YOU, GEORGE!

11:05.736 --> 11:09.770
YOU DON´T KNOW HOW MUCH THIS
 MEANS TO ME!

11:09.770 --> 11:13.744
THIS IS THE GREATEST MOMENT
 OF MY LIFE!

11:13.744 --> 11:16.807
THAT´S...
 THAT´S SAD, BRO.

11:17.808 --> 11:19.679
ANGIE,
 WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:19.679 --> 11:21.812
JOE PASSED AWAY.

11:21.812 --> 11:23.083
OH, DAMN.

11:23.083 --> 11:25.055
IS BENNY AROUND?

11:25.055 --> 11:27.687
YEAH.

11:27.687 --> 11:30.020
MOM, COULD YOU COME
 IN HERE, PLEASE?

11:35.195 --> 11:37.167
I´M SORRY, MOM.
 JOE´S GONE.

11:37.167 --> 11:41.371
THEY CALLED ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.
 THE FUNERAL´S THIS SUNDAY.

11:41.371 --> 11:44.935
WELL, AT LEAST HE´S NOT
 SUFFERING ANYMORE.

11:44.935 --> 11:46.036
SUPER BOWL SUNDAY?

11:47.738 --> 11:51.111
YEAH, I KNOW THAT SUCKS,
 BUT WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

11:51.111 --> 11:54.785
WE´LL ALL DRIVE DOWN TO THE
 FUNERAL TOGETHER.

11:59.820 --> 12:02.022
I CAN´T GO
 TO THE FUNERAL.

12:02.022 --> 12:04.024
YOU HAVE TO!

12:04.024 --> 12:05.756
NO, I CAN´T.

12:05.756 --> 12:07.327
OKAY, OKAY,
 HOW ABOUT THIS --

12:07.327 --> 12:09.960
YOU GO TO THE FUNERAL, YOU SEE
 JOE, AND THEN YOU CAN LEAVE

12:09.960 --> 12:12.162
AND STILL GET TO THE GAME IN
 TIME FOR KICKOFF.

12:12.162 --> 12:14.364
I´M SURE YOUR MOM
 WILL BE FINE WITH THAT.

12:14.364 --> 12:16.406
NO, I DON´T WANT TO GO.

12:16.406 --> 12:18.068
WHY ARE YOU BEING
 LIKE THIS?

12:18.068 --> 12:20.310
´CAUSE I DON´T WANT TO GO
 TO THE FUNERAL.

12:20.310 --> 12:21.741
WHAT IS THE BIG DEAL?

12:21.741 --> 12:23.473
I DON´T WANT TO SEE
 DEAD PEOPLE,

12:23.473 --> 12:25.876
AND I DON´T WANT TO
 SEE PEOPLE CRYING,

12:25.876 --> 12:28.318
AND I DON´T WANT TO
 TALK ABOUT THIS ANYMORE.

12:31.952 --> 12:33.283
HEY, I KNOW YOU.

12:33.283 --> 12:35.255
YOU GOT ME THIS JOB.

12:35.255 --> 12:36.827
THAT´S RIGHT.

12:36.827 --> 12:40.060
I SHOULD KICK YOUR ASS
 RIGHT HERE!

12:50.841 --> 12:53.944
I GOT THE KIDS SOME CLOTHES
 FOR THE FUNERAL ON SUNDAY.

12:53.944 --> 12:55.946
YOU WANT ME TO PRESS
 YOUR BLACK SUIT

12:55.946 --> 12:57.477
IN CASE YOU CHANGE
 YOUR MIND?

12:57.477 --> 12:59.079
NO.

12:59.079 --> 13:01.111
YOU KNOW,
 SOMETIMES WHEN I SAY

13:01.111 --> 13:04.154
I DON´T WANT TO TALK
 ABOUT SOMETHING,

13:04.154 --> 13:08.058
IT MEANS THAT´S WHAT I REALLY
 WANT TO TALK ABOUT THE MOST.

13:08.058 --> 13:10.290
YEAH,
 I HATE THAT ABOUT YOU.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.963
COME ON, CARMEN AND MAX
 ARE BOTH GOING.

13:12.963 --> 13:16.066
IT´S GONNA BE HARD TO EXPLAIN TO
 THEM WHY YOU´RE NOT.

13:16.066 --> 13:17.968
WHY ARE YOU TAKING
 THE KIDS?

13:17.968 --> 13:20.831
I DON´T THINK THEY HAVE TO
 GO THROUGH ALL THAT.

13:20.831 --> 13:22.072
GO THROUGH ALL WHAT?

13:22.072 --> 13:24.134
YOU KNOW,
 WHEN YOU SEE THE COFFIN,

13:24.134 --> 13:26.576
AND YOU THINK ABOUT YOUR BODY
 ROTTING AWAY

13:26.576 --> 13:28.108
AND YOUR EYES
 SHRIVELING UP,

13:28.108 --> 13:30.140
AND YOUR NAILS ARE STILL
 GROWING.

13:30.140 --> 13:32.582
ANGIE, YOUR NAILS NEVER
 STOP GROWING!

13:32.582 --> 13:34.314
GEORGE,
 THEY STOP GROWING.

13:34.314 --> 13:37.387
IF THEY DIDN´T STOP GROWING,
 EVERYWHERE YOU WENT,

13:37.387 --> 13:41.021
THERE´D BE FINGERNAILS SHOOTING
 UP OUT OF THE GROUND.

13:41.021 --> 13:43.493
YOU DON´T GET IT.

13:44.224 --> 13:46.126
WHAT´S HIS PROBLEM?

13:46.126 --> 13:48.158
HE WON´T GO
 TO THE FUNERAL.

13:48.158 --> 13:49.259
DAMN.

13:49.259 --> 13:50.901
I SHOULD HAVE SEEN
 THIS COMING.

13:50.901 --> 13:52.462
WHAT?

13:52.462 --> 13:55.835
OH, HE´S SCARED OF DEATH EVER
 SINCE HE WAS A KID.

13:55.835 --> 13:58.939
HE NEVER TOLD ME THAT.
 DID SOMETHING HAPPEN?

13:58.939 --> 14:00.510
OH,
 JUST THE KIND OF STUFF

14:00.510 --> 14:03.543
THAT REALLY IS OUT OF
 A PARENT´S CONTROL.

14:03.543 --> 14:05.315
LIKE WHAT?

14:05.315 --> 14:06.877
LIKE I LIED TO HIM

14:06.877 --> 14:10.080
AND TOLD HIM THAT HIS DAD
 DIED WHEN HE WAS 4.

14:10.080 --> 14:11.882
THAT PROBABLY DIDN´T HELP.

14:11.882 --> 14:13.023
UH-HUH.

14:13.023 --> 14:15.225
AND THEN HE WAS REALLY
 SCARED,

14:15.225 --> 14:18.028
AND HE ASKED ME
 IF HE WAS EVER GONNA DIE.

14:18.028 --> 14:20.230
AND WHAT DID YOU SAY?

14:20.230 --> 14:21.331
I SAID, "NO."

14:21.331 --> 14:23.433
I SAID,
 "WHEN YOU GROW UP,

14:23.433 --> 14:26.496
"THEY WILL HAVE CURED
 ALL OF THE DISEASES,

14:26.496 --> 14:29.099
AND YOU´RE GONNA LIVE
 FOREVER."

14:29.099 --> 14:32.502
BUT THAT ONE WASN´T MY FAULT.
 SCIENCE LET ME DOWN.

14:32.502 --> 14:34.174
BENNY,
 YOU MESSED HIM UP!

14:34.174 --> 14:37.347
HE NEVER LEARNED HOW TO HANDLE
 DEATH AS A CHILD,

14:37.347 --> 14:39.509
AND NOW HE CAN´T HANDLE
 IT AS AN ADULT.

14:39.509 --> 14:42.252
I KNOW.
 I´M GONNA TALK TO HIM.

14:42.252 --> 14:45.355
IT´S TIME HE WENT TO HIS
 FIRST FUNERAL.

14:45.355 --> 14:48.318
HE NEVER WENT EVEN
 WHEN HE WAS YOUNGER?

14:48.318 --> 14:49.960
WELL,
 THEY NEVER INVITED US.

14:49.960 --> 14:52.923
I WAS ALWAYS HAVING FIGHTS
 WITH ALL OF THE RELATIVES.

14:52.923 --> 14:56.967
YOU KNOW, EVEN MY COUSIN RUDY
 HAD IT PUT ON HIS TOMBSTONE --

14:56.967 --> 15:00.670
"IF YOU CAN READ THIS,
 BENNY LOPEZ, YOU´RE TOO CLOSE."

15:11.341 --> 15:14.945
GEORGE,
 I GOTTA TALK TO YOU.

15:14.945 --> 15:16.386
WHAT´S WITH THE DRESS?

15:16.386 --> 15:19.019
THIS IS THE DRESS
 I WANT TO BE BURIED IN.

15:19.019 --> 15:20.390
REALLY?

15:20.390 --> 15:23.253
THAT´S THE DRESS YOU WANT
 GOD TO SEE YOU IN

15:23.253 --> 15:25.295
THE FIRST TIME YOU MEET?

15:25.295 --> 15:26.997
I´M NOT KIDDING.

15:26.997 --> 15:28.999
THIS IS MY DEATH DRESS.

15:28.999 --> 15:33.133
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA WEAR FOR
 THE SWIMSUIT COMPETITION?

15:33.133 --> 15:37.037
LISTEN, GEORGE, YOU HELPED ME
 GET THROUGH SOMETHING.

15:37.037 --> 15:38.638
NOW I´M GONNA HELP YOU.

15:38.638 --> 15:42.312
YOU KNOW, THE BEST WAY TO GET
 RID OF YOUR FEAR OF DEATH

15:42.312 --> 15:43.713
IS TAKE CONTROL OF IT!

15:43.713 --> 15:45.575
LIKE ME.
 I GOT EVERYTHING PLANNED.

15:45.575 --> 15:47.117
MOM,
 I DON´T WANT TO DO THIS.

15:47.117 --> 15:49.179
COME ON, GEORGE.
 COME ON, PAY ATTENTION.

15:49.179 --> 15:50.580
YOU´RE THE ONLY ONE
 I TRUST,

15:50.580 --> 15:53.183
AND I´M GONNA MAKE SURE
 THAT YOU´RE IN CHARGE

15:53.183 --> 15:54.524
OF ALL OF MY ARRANGEMENTS,
 OKAY?

15:54.524 --> 15:57.387
NUMBER ONE --
 MAKE SURE I´M DEAD.

15:57.387 --> 15:59.459
NUMBER TWO --

15:59.459 --> 16:03.033
MAKE SURE I´M DEAD.

16:03.033 --> 16:06.396
NUMBER THREE -- DO NOT LET THEM
 PUT ME IN THE GROUND

16:06.396 --> 16:08.638
WITHOUT DOING MY EYE MAKEUP,
 OKAY?

16:08.638 --> 16:12.202
AND I WOULD LIKE FOR IT TO BE
 POWDER BLUE TO MATCH MY GOWN.

16:12.202 --> 16:16.076
OH, AND ALSO, YOU KNOW,
 HAVE THEM ARCH MY EYEBROWS,

16:16.076 --> 16:19.609
BUT NOT TOO MUCH SO I DON´T LOOK
 LIKE I´M SURPRISED,

16:19.609 --> 16:22.252
LIKE SOMEBODY GOT ME FROM
 BEHIND.

16:22.252 --> 16:24.014
COME ON, MOM!
 YOU´RE CREEPING ME OUT!

16:24.014 --> 16:26.056
YOU´RE NOT GONNA DIE FOR
 A LONG, LONG TIME!

16:26.056 --> 16:27.417
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

16:27.417 --> 16:29.189
THIS IS WHAT IT´S GONNA
 LOOK LIKE.

16:29.189 --> 16:30.460
OH, BUT NOT EXACTLY.

16:30.460 --> 16:32.422
I DON´T WANT TO BE BURIED
 IN A BRA.

16:32.422 --> 16:34.464
THESE THINGS HURT AFTER
 FOUR HOURS.

16:34.464 --> 16:36.296
COME ON, MOM, STOP IT.
 GET UP.

16:36.296 --> 16:40.370
NO, NO, I´M JUST SAYING PICTURE
 THEM MORE TO THE SIDES.

16:40.370 --> 16:42.772
OKAY, OKAY!
 I´LL GO TO JOE´S FUNERAL!

16:42.772 --> 16:44.204
JUST GET UP!

16:44.204 --> 16:46.706
MOM, I DON´T WANT TO PICTURE
 YOU DEAD.

16:46.706 --> 16:48.508
GOOD.

16:48.508 --> 16:51.241
YOU FEEL BETTER?

16:51.241 --> 16:54.144
NO, BUT I´LL BE OKAY.

16:59.049 --> 17:01.451
SO...

17:01.451 --> 17:04.394
I GUESS YOU´RE GONNA BE SAD
 WHEN I GO, HUH?

17:04.394 --> 17:05.625
OF COURSE.
 YOU´RE MY MOM.

17:05.625 --> 17:08.027
BUT THAT´S A LONG, LONG WAY
 DOWN THE ROAD.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.299
OH, YEAH, YEAH.

17:09.299 --> 17:12.262
YEAH,
 I´M SURE YOU´RE RIGHT.

17:12.262 --> 17:13.703
UH-OH.

17:13.703 --> 17:16.766
WHAT´S THIS RIGHT HERE?

17:16.766 --> 17:20.240
I GOT A --
 I GOT A LITTLE BUMP ON MY NECK.

17:20.240 --> 17:21.810
OH, CUT IT OUT, MOM!

17:21.810 --> 17:24.144
OH, I´M GONNA DIE.

17:24.144 --> 17:25.675
I´M GONNA DIE.

17:25.675 --> 17:27.217
KEEP IT UP, MOM!

17:27.217 --> 17:29.779
YOU´RE THIS CLOSE TO WEARING
 BROWN EYE SHADOW

17:29.779 --> 17:31.050
AND A HEFTY BAG!

17:31.050 --> 17:33.723
[ COUGHING ]

17:33.723 --> 17:35.685
UH-OH.

17:46.696 --> 17:48.598
WELL...

17:48.598 --> 17:51.671
THAT´S IT.

17:51.671 --> 17:53.243
COME ON, GEORGE.

17:53.243 --> 17:54.544
LET´S GO.

17:54.544 --> 17:58.748
I THINK I WANT TO SAY
 GOODBYE TO JOE.

17:58.748 --> 18:01.151
YOU SURE?

18:03.683 --> 18:05.385
YEAH.

18:05.385 --> 18:08.388
WELL, YOU KNOW, IT SORT
 OF REEKS OF DEATH IN HERE.

18:08.388 --> 18:10.690
I´M GONNA GO OUT
 AND HAVE A SMOKE.

18:18.828 --> 18:22.772
SO...JOE...

18:22.772 --> 18:25.135
NICE RIDE.

18:26.876 --> 18:30.710
WELL, I GUESS THIS IS IT.

18:30.710 --> 18:32.612
GOODBYE.

18:36.746 --> 18:38.418
OH, HELL.

18:43.493 --> 18:46.296
WOW.

18:46.296 --> 18:49.599
I SEE WHAT MY MOM MEANT
 ABOUT THE EYEBROWS.

18:51.501 --> 18:54.234
JOE, YOU WERE
 AN ALL-RIGHT UNCLE.

18:54.234 --> 18:56.736
THANK YOU FOR MAKING UP
 WITH MY MOM.

18:56.736 --> 18:59.739
HEY, MAN, I KNOW YOU DIDN´T WANT
 TO MISS THE SUPER BOWL.

18:59.739 --> 19:03.343
SO...

19:03.343 --> 19:05.715
[ CROWD CHEERING
 ON TELEVISION ]

19:05.715 --> 19:07.677
THERE YOU GO, TIO.

19:09.879 --> 19:14.254
[ CROWD CHEERING ]

19:14.254 --> 19:15.585
YES!

19:15.585 --> 19:16.686
GO!

19:16.686 --> 19:18.658
OH!

19:18.658 --> 19:20.830
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

19:20.830 --> 19:24.163
[ Voice breaking ]
 I´M NOT READY TO LEAVE HIM YET.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.835
COULD YOU GIVE ME
 A MINUTE?

19:31.571 --> 19:33.273
FUMBLE!

19:33.273 --> 19:34.604
OH...

19:34.604 --> 19:36.676
[ SNIFFLES ]

19:36.676 --> 19:39.449
WHY?

19:44.314 --> 19:46.256
HERE, JOE,
 LET ME FIX THE PICTURE FOR YOU.

19:46.256 --> 19:47.417
THERE.

19:50.460 --> 19:52.522
OH, YEAH!

19:52.522 --> 19:53.563
WHOO!

19:53.563 --> 19:55.325
FUMBLE!

19:55.325 --> 19:56.596
OH!

19:56.596 --> 19:59.499
WHERE´S THE FLAG?!

19:59.499 --> 20:00.470
OH...

20:00.470 --> 20:02.902
NO FLAG!

20:02.902 --> 20:05.204
OH...

20:05.204 --> 20:06.776
HEY.

20:06.776 --> 20:09.339
OH, HEY, THANKS.

20:09.339 --> 20:11.741
YOU KNOW, SOME CHIPS
 WOULD BE NICE.
